## Steps

### step 1
id: navigate-to-locations
instruction: Click "Locations" in the main sidebar, or open an account and click the "Locations" tab on the account detail page.
success_criteria: You are on the Locations page showing a table of existing locations with columns for Name, Facility NPI, Tax ID, Address, POS, Providers, and Status.
anchor: locations-nav-link
on_success: next
on_stuck: The "Locations" link is in the left sidebar. Alternatively, go to Accounts, open an account, and click the Locations tab.

### step 2
id: click-add-location
instruction: Click the "Add Location" button.
success_criteria: The Add Location form has opened with fields for Location Name, Facility NPI, Facility Tax ID, Service Address, Default Place of Service, and Active Providers.
anchor: add-location-button
on_success: next
on_stuck: The button is at the top right of the Locations page.

### step 3
id: enter-location-name-and-npi
instruction: Enter a descriptive Location Name your team will recognize (required). Optionally enter the Facility NPI — a 10-digit number assigned to this site.
success_criteria: Location Name is filled in. Facility NPI is entered if applicable.
anchor: location-name-field
on_success: next
on_stuck: Location Name is the only required field. The NPI field accepts exactly 10 digits.

### step 4
id: enter-address-and-pos
instruction: Enter the full Service Address (street, city, two-letter state code, 5-digit ZIP). Select the Default Place of Service code for this site — for example, 11 for Office, 22 for Outpatient Hospital, or 24 for Ambulatory Surgical Center.
success_criteria: Address fields are complete. A Place of Service code is selected from the dropdown.
anchor: service-address-field
on_success: next
on_stuck: Click the Place of Service dropdown and select the code that best describes this location type.

### step 5
id: save-location
instruction: Optionally check which providers practice at this location, then click "Save" (or equivalent) to create the location.
success_criteria: The new location appears in the Locations table with Active status. Its name, address, and POS code are correct.
anchor: save-location-button
on_success: completion
on_stuck: Fill in any required fields that are highlighted, then click Save.

## Completion Message
location added! it's now available when creating claims from that site. make sure the right providers are linked to this location so Altair can apply the correct billing rules.

